# Frontend & Backend Coding Standards ‚Äî Support Ticket Management System

Internal support ticket tool: authenticated users (`agent` / `admin`) create, update, comment on, search, and progress tickets through an enforced status lifecycle; admins manage users. Frontend in `frontend/` (React 19, Vite 6, Zustand 5, Tailwind CSS 4), backend in `backend/` (Node.js 22, Express 5, TypeScript 5.x, `pg`), data in PostgreSQL.

This file is the **overview**. Defer to the scoped rules when they go deeper:
- Backend details ‚Üí `nodejs-backend-patterns.mdc`
- SQL / schema ‚Üí `database-standards.mdc`
- Types / Zod ‚Üí `typescript-strict.mdc`
- React / Zustand ‚Üí `react19-standards.mdc`
- Tailwind ‚Üí `tailwind-standards.mdc`

Auth (JWT + roles) is **in scope for this project** even though the exercise marks it Stretch ‚Äî implement it.

## Architecture

**Backend layers** (`backend/src/`): routes ‚Üí services ‚Üí repositories. Routes own HTTP + Zod validation only. Services own business logic (`TicketStatusService` owns the entire status state machine). Repositories own SQL via `pg` ‚Äî never query the DB from a route. Never skip a layer.

**Frontend state**: five Zustand stores ‚Äî `authStore`, `ticketStore`, `userStore`, `filterStore`, `uiStore`. Stores hold data + async API wrappers; **no business rules** (status transitions are server-enforced; UI only filters which buttons to show). Data loading is store-driven (see `react19-standards.mdc`), not Suspense/`use(Promise)`-first.

**Naming**: TypeScript and JSON APIs use `camelCase`. PostgreSQL columns use `snake_case`. Map at the repository boundary (`assigned_to` ‚Üí `assignedTo`). Never leak `passwordHash` / `password_hash` past the repository/service boundary.

## Security & API (summary)

- Validate every request body, query param, and route param with Zod at the route boundary; derive types with `z.infer`; strip unknown keys.
- Persist **plain text only** for `title`, `description`, `message` ‚Äî Zod length limits; reject values containing `<` or `>`. Do **not** run an HTML sanitizer library on store. Frontend renders with normal React text children ‚Äî never `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` for user content.
- Parameterized SQL only (`$1`, `$2`, ‚Ä¶). Passwords: `await bcrypt.hash(password, 12)` (cost ‚â• 10). Random IDs/tokens: `node:crypto` (`randomUUID`, etc.) ‚Äî bcrypt is the exception for password hashing.
- Protected routes: `authenticateToken` then optional `requireRole('admin')`. JWT payload `{ sub, email, role, iat, exp }`, 24h expiry. `JWT_SECRET` and `DATABASE_URL` from env only (validated at boot).
- Error wire format (success returns the resource/data directly): `{ error: string, code: string, details?: unknown }` with matching HTTP status (400 / 401 / 403 / 404 / 409 / 429 / 500).
- Rate-limit `POST /api/auth/login`: **10 requests / 15 min / IP** (all attempts) ‚Üí 429. CORS allowlist = `FRONTEND_ORIGIN` only. Use `helmet` + explicit CORS (details in backend rules).
- Authorization model: any authenticated `agent` or `admin` may read/update any ticket and comment (internal tool). User CRUD is `admin` only. `GET /api/users` is available to both roles (assignee picker).

## Frontend UX (summary)

- `authStore` keeps JWT in `sessionStorage`, attaches `Authorization: Bearer`, clears + redirects to `/login` on 401.
- Every store-driven fetch exposes loading/error in the store or `uiStore`. Forms use React 19 `useActionState` where they submit; comments/status use `useOptimistic` with rollback on 409.
- Status buttons only for valid transitions: `Open` ‚Üí In Progress / Cancelled; `In Progress` ‚Üí Resolved / Cancelled; `Resolved` ‚Üí Closed; `Closed` / `Cancelled` ‚Üí none. Show 409 inline, no reload.
- Admin-only nav/routes render only **when** `role === 'admin'` (hide, don‚Äôt disable); wait until session restore finishes before rendering role-dependent UI.
- Accessibility: keyboard-navigable controls, labeled inputs, `aria-live` for errors, WCAG 2.1 AA contrast, focus trap in modals.

## Code Quality Checks

1. ‚úÖ Zod at every route input; types from `z.infer`
2. ‚úÖ Parameterized SQL only; snake_case ‚Üî camelCase in repositories
3. ‚úÖ No `passwordHash` in any API response or client type
4. ‚úÖ Loading + error states for async UI; 409 shown inline for bad transitions
5. ‚úÖ Status changes only via `TicketStatusService` / `PATCH .../status`
6. ‚úÖ `authenticateToken` / `requireRole('admin')` on the right routes
7. ‚úÖ No secrets in source ‚Äî env validated at startup
8. ‚úÖ Tailwind utilities only (plus the single Tailwind v4 CSS entry file)
